weetzie bat i know it's a kid book but i loved it and i want to know i've recently found the time to read more again and i was wondering if you've read and enjoyed weetzie bat what other books do you like what are you reading now i love weetzie bat as someone else already suggested if you haven't already read the rest of the weetzie bat collection you should try that you can find all but the most recent book in the collection dangerous angels the newest one is called necklace of kisses also the rest of block's books are just as awesome as weetzie my particular favorites are i was a teenage fairy wasteland and psyche in a dress there is also echo violet claire girl goddess rose and the beast ruby ecstasia primavera and the hanged man i love her style as for other authors holly black's tithe is good there are two other sequels but i haven't read them yet the china garden by liz berry is excellent all the books by tamora pierce are great starting with the song of the lioness quartet and progressing through her tortall series i love robin mckinley as well espeially the hero and the crown and the blue sword for something a little more adult marion zimmer bradley's the mists of avalon is wonderful the thursday next series by jasper fforde as well as his nursery crimes series are hillarious tolkein's lord of the rings is a slow read but worth the effort besides block jane austen is another favorite of mine i especially love pride and prejudice and persuasion others i have enjoyed recently blonde by joyce carol oates kindred by octavia butler nothing like the sun by anthony burgess ender's game by orson scott card the sound and the fury by william faulkner and slaughterhouse five by kurt vonnegut currently i'm rereading the harry potter series as well as working my way through darwin's origin of species Young adult literature Academy Award for Original Music Score Marion Zimmer Bradley Francesca Lia Block Joyce Carol Oates Novel AVN Awards Cardcaptor Sakura Children's liter